me for a criminal.

146
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:43,833
Man, why do nice guys
have to finish last?

147
00:07:43,916 --> 00:07:46,416
Oh. They're jealous. Duh.

148
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,333
You're wrong! This
isn't how it looks!

149
00:07:51,041 --> 00:07:53,208
I've seen this in movies.

150
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:54,541
You know, where the
scary guy says,

151
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:56,708
"Whadda ya lookin' at?" and
freaks everyone out.

152
00:07:56,791 --> 00:07:59,125
I've never seen it in
real life before, though.

153
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,333
They were the ones who
wanted to come along.

154
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:06,166
Why do I always have
to be the bad guy?

155
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:19,916
What's up, stalker?

156
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:25,583
Uh. What the hell is that?

157
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:26,833
I'm giving you my wallet

158
00:08:26,916 --> 00:08:28,625
this is your standard
shakedown, isn't it?

159
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:30,750
No!

160
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:32,541
My name is
Yukimura Kusnoki.

161
00:08:32,625 --> 00:08:34,708
I'm in Class 1-1.

162
00:08:34,791 --> 00:08:36,708
Wait; isn't that a
famous samurai's name?

163
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:38,083
That's right.

164
00:08:38,166 --> 00:08:40,083
He's from the Warring
States period.

165
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:41,833
My parents chose it for
me because they wanted me

166
00:08:41,916 --> 00:08:43,250
to become a son they
could be proud of,

167
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:45,625
just like Yukimura Sanada's
parents had been.

168
00:08:45,708 --> 00:08:47,750
A son? Really?

169
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,833
Yes. I'm obviously a boy,

170
00:08:49,916 --> 00:08:51,041
so that would make sense.

171
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:54,041
Uh. You are not
obviously anything.

172
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:55,666
So what's the deal with
following me around

173
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:56,875
all the damn time?

174
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:58,541
To tell you the truth.

175
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,333
I'm a sad victim
of bullying.

176
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,208
Bullying?

177
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:05,166
You guys have bullies
at this school.

178
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,625
-I didn't know.
-How could you not?

179
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:08,375
There're no schools
without bullies.

180
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:14,208
What are they
bullying you about?

181
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:15,625
Or do you even know?

182
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,125
They do it
because it's fun.

183
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:18,916
It's fun?

184
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,625
People just enjoy
attacking others

185
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:23,666
when they know they're not going
to get hurt in the process.

186
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,500
Like killing
living animals.

187
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:27,750
Or torturing
somebody online.

188
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:30,375
But it's the person who's
getting bullied's fault.

189
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:31,916
The bully would stop if
they wouldn't react

190
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,541
and give them
something to enjoy.

191
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:35,375
And that's straight
from the horse's mouth.

192
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:39,833
How dare you assume I'm
the same as those cowards!

193
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,250
Anyway. What's the deal?

194
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:47,833
How come you were
following Kodaka.

195
00:09:47,916 --> 00:09:49,000
Right.

196
